The governments of the Netherlands nationalize a part of Fortis Bank.
The states of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization of the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis of the North American market: the three countries will support in total with 11.2 billion euros to this financial and insurance institution that also has business in Hungary.
This weekend, the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held high-level consultations with the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commission’s economic competition officer.
Fortis Bank is the first to suffer from the eurozone crisis in the context of the international financial crisis that has been occurring in several waves more than a year ago, therefore the decisions taken with regard to the Bank, in a sense, can be considered as precedents.
According to the decision made in the early hours of Sunday, the three states will buy about half (49 percent) of the property owned by the Bank in their area.
The Bank will certainly sell a part of its business, including mainly the activities – mainly insurance – purchased last year from the Dutch ABN Amro.
Fortis’ actions began a sharp decline last week and for the second half of the week there were already significant signs of crisis in the institution.
However, analysts agree to point out that with its 85,000 employees this bank is too big to allow it to go bankrupt.
The company’s shares fell 12 percent on Friday alone, the lowest in 14 years.
Since January, the value of the shares has decreased by more than two-thirds.
Looking at the current share prices, the total value of the group’s capital in the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to the company’s executives this is not real.
The bank’s management blamed the sharp fall in Fortis shares on the insecurities of the US market in connection with the approval of the US $700 billion package plan.
On Monday, the stocks showed already a slight increase.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx was appointed as the bank’s new CEO.
The Bank also sought private investors, but so far no one has made a concrete offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured investors that they would not have to worry, they would not lose their money.
Among the Bank’s clients so far, no panic occurred, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also purchased leasing companies.
Zorro in the chicken coop
In the U.S., life and health insurance companies often refuse to sign an insurance contract when they see the data on drug purchases.
The privacy policy specialists fear that the personal data market will become uncontrollable.
"There are programs for the protection of personal data, which binds the use of recipe data in all cases to the approval of the given person.
The same must be in independent hands, because if not, "we entrust the henhouse to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post to Richard Dick, designer of the medical prescription tracking program.
Insurance companies make the price of the insurance and the amount of reimbursement of the customer’s health condition dependent and if they believe the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
Earlier they sent the client to medical examination and signed the contract with him already knowing the result of the examination.
Dick invented a much cheaper procedure ten years ago: with the customer identification number he easily obtains from pharmacies the list of drugs purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the diseases and health of the customer.
For example, if you systematically take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that your blood fat level is practically incurably high, so you are immediately included in a higher risk category.
Numerous versions of the program circulate, some even set a number of risks, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has hardly anything to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the disadvantages of the program is, for example, that some medications are multipurpose, for example, certain substances serve both to treat headaches and for heat waves and even as antidepressants.
The latter is an important risk-increasing factor for insurance companies while the former is not.
Special companies were established to consult and process this data, which before acquiring the necessary information from pharmacies, ask for the approval of the patient.
Authorities are already forcing them to do so, although they have not been fined for negligence so far.
Some companies also recently compile the results of lab tests and by combining them with drug consumption data they get more accurate information about the patient’s state of health.
More and more company have access to this data and at the same time it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those providing health services.
The Congress is already before the draft law that gives the authority for control of companies specializing in the provision of personal data.
Dick Richard acknowledges that this is insufficient: therefore he developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that such a person cannot deny his approval, because if not, the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So the chickens, after all, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
